yearn /jɜːn/

(yearning,yearned,yearns) 

1. V-T/V-I If someone yearns for something that they are unlikely to get, they want it very much. 渴望 

例： He yearned for freedom. 他曾渴望自由。 

例： I yearned to be an actor. 我曾渴望成为一名演员。

